    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2018-05-14</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2019-12-13T20:50:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Preventing Drug Diversion Act of 2018</b> </p> <p>This bill establishes a new requirement intended to help drug manufacturers and distributors identify and prevent suspicious orders of opioids and reduce rates of diversion.</p> <p>Specifically, the Drug Enforcement Administration must use its automated data system&#8212;the Automated Reports and Consolidated Ordering System&#8212;to inform drug manufacturers and distributors about the quantity and type of opioids that are distributed to pharmacies and practitioners.</p> <p>Additionally, the bill establishes new requirements for reporting, collecting, and sharing information about suspicious orders.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
